---
layout: base.njk
title: "MakeChatt: a community for makers in Chattanooga, TN"
---
<header class="site-header">
  <div class="wrap">
    <a class="brand" href="#top">
      <img src="/assets/images/makechatt-logo-ink.svg" alt="">
      <span>MAKE<em>CHATT</em></span>
    </a>
    <nav class="site-nav">
      <a class="stamp stamp--solid" href="{{ discordUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Discord</a>
    </nav>
  </div>
</header>

<main id="top">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow stamp hero-tag">Chattanooga's Online Makerspace</span>
      <h1 class="misprint">A community for makers in Chattanooga, TN</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Whether you're a pro, just starting out, or tinkering in your garage,
        MakeChatt is a place for Chattanooga makers, crafters, and artists to
        learn from each other and build stuff together.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="stamp stamp--solid" href="{{ discordUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Join the Discord</a>
      </div>
      <img class="hero-mark" src="/assets/images/makechatt-logo-ink.svg" alt="">
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="torn torn--ink"></div>

  <section class="mission">
    <div class="halftone"></div>
    <span class="mission-mark">&rdquo;</span>
    <div class="wrap mission-inner">
      <blockquote>
        Chattanooga is full of creative people, and I want to make a place to help
        each other learn new skills and make new things.
      </blockquote>
      <div class="mission-values">
        <span class="badge">Inclusive</span>
        <span class="badge">No fees</span>
        <span class="badge">No memberships</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="torn torn--dim"></div>

  <section class="guidelines" id="guidelines">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">House rules</span>
      <h2>Community guidelines</h2>
      <ul class="guideline-list">
        <li>Everyone deserves to create, regardless of gender, race, ethnicity, religion, sexual orientation, identity, or background.</li>
        <li>Hate has no place here. Sexism, racism, homophobia, transphobia, harassment, or discrimination of any kind will not be tolerated.</li>
        <li>Be kind, respectful, and patient. Everyone starts somewhere.</li>
        <li>Share your knowledge freely, and don't be afraid to ask questions.</li>
        <li>Respect each other's time, tools, creations, and personal space.</li>
        <li>Help build a community where everyone feels welcome.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq" id="faq">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">Good to know</span>
      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is there a cost to join?</summary>
          <p>Nope. MakeChatt is free, no memberships, no fees, ever.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do I need experience to join?</summary>
          <p>Not at all. Pro, novice, or home-lab tinkerer, everyone's welcome here.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Where does MakeChatt actually happen?</summary>
          <p>Mostly on Discord. That's where project threads, questions, tool
          swaps, and meetup planning happen.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Who's behind this?</summary>
          <div class="faq-person">
            <img class="about-photo" src="/assets/images/don.png" alt="Donald Sayers, MakeChatt founder">
            <div>
              <p class="faq-person-name">Donald Sayers (he/him)</p>
              <p>I love making things and picking up new skills, and it turns out
              I'm not the only one. Chattanooga's full of woodworkers, welders,
              coders, sewists, potters, and home-lab tinkerers. We're all over
              this city, mostly just doing our own thing.</p>
              <p>MakeChatt is about getting us in the same room, or at least the
              same Discord server, so we can teach each other, swap tools and
              know-how, and make more than we would on our own.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do I get started?</summary>
          <p>Jump in the <a href="{{ discordUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Discord</a> and say hi. That's it.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>

<footer class="site-footer">
  <div class="wrap">
